Preconditions:
The grid parameter must be a 2-dimensional array of integers.
The grid must contain at least one row and one column.
Each element in the grid must be either 0 (representing a water cell) or a positive integer (representing the number of fish in a cell).

Postconditions:
The method returns an integer value representing the maximum number of fish the fisher can catch.
If no water cell exists in the grid, the method returns 0.